Ginger Beer

5oz    fresh ginger
4 tbsp brown sugar
2-3    lemons
4 c    soda water or sparkling mineral water
springs of fresh mint

Grate ginger.  Put ginger and juice into a bowl and sprinkle with brown
sugar.  Remove rind from 2 lemons with vegetable peeler and add to bowl.
Bash and squash lemon/ginger mixture for 10 seconds.  Squeeze juice from
3 lemons and add most of it to the bowl.  Pour in fizzy water.  Allow to
sit for 10 minutes and then taste and add sugar or lemon juice as needed.
Pour through coarse sieve into large pitcher, add lots of ice and springs
of mint.
